From: CIX OSS <oss@cixtech.com>
Subject: Move use_sky1_dma_pause and timeout_value outside CONFIG_DMA_ENGINE ifdef

The CIX BSP patch 0046 adds use_sky1_dma_pause and timeout_value fields to
struct uart_amba_port inside the #ifdef CONFIG_DMA_ENGINE block, but
references them from code outside that block. When CONFIG_DMA_ENGINE is not
enabled (e.g. Debian arm64 cloud config), compilation fails with:
  error: 'struct uart_amba_port' has no member named 'use_sky1_dma_pause'

Move the two field definitions outside the #ifdef to fix this.

--- a/drivers/tty/serial/amba-pl011.c
+++ b/drivers/tty/serial/amba-pl011.c
@@ -321,9 +321,9 @@
 	struct pl011_dmarx_data dmarx;
 	struct pl011_dmatx_data	dmatx;
 	bool			dma_probed;
+#endif
 	bool use_sky1_dma_pause;
 	unsigned int timeout_value;
-#endif
 };

 static unsigned int pl011_tx_empty(struct uart_port *port);
